#: ../../manual/modeling/texts/introduction.rst:13
msgid ""
"*Text* objects contain some text, and share the same object type as *Curves* and *Surfaces*, as modern fonts are "
"vectorial, made of curves."
msgstr "*文本* 物体包含文本。由于现代字体是矢量化的，由曲线构成，因此其与 *曲线* 和 *曲面* 为同一物体类型。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/texts/introduction.rst:17
msgid ""
"Blender uses a \"Font System\" to manage mapping letter codes to objects representing them in 3D views. This font "
"system has its own *built-in* font, but it can use external fonts too, including *PostScript Type 1*, *OpenType* and "
"*TrueType* fonts. And moreover, it can use any objects existing in the current blend-file as letters."
msgstr ""
"Blender使用一套 \"字体\" 来管理文字符号到3D视图中物体的映射关系。该字体系统有自己 *内建* 的字体，但也可以使用外部字体，"
"如 *PostScript Type 1*, *OpenType* 与 *TrueType* 字体。另外，它可以使用当前blend文件中的任何物体表示字符。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/texts/introduction.rst:25
msgid "An example of an extruded text."
msgstr "例: 挤出后的字体。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/texts/introduction.rst:27
msgid ""
"*Text* objects allow you to create and render 2D or 3D text, with various advanced layout options, like justifying and "
"frames. By default, letters are just flat filled surfaces, exactly like any closed 2D curve. But, just like *Curves*, "
"you can extrude them. And texts can follow other curves."
msgstr ""
"*文本* 物体用于使用各种布局选项如排版和框架，来创建和渲染二维或三维文本。字符默认为平面填充的曲面，和闭合二维曲线一样。"
"但是，跟 *曲线* 一样，可以对其进行挤出。文本还可设置为跟随曲线。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/texts/introduction.rst:32
msgid "You can convert *Text*, either to a curve, or directly to a mesh, with :kbd:`Alt-C` in *Object Mode*."
msgstr "可以在 *物体模式* 下使用 :kbd:`Alt-C` 将 *文本* 转换为 *曲线*，或者直接转换为网格。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/texts/introduction.rst:37
msgid ""
"A maximum of 50000 characters is allowed per text object; however, be forewarned that the more characters a single "
"text object has, the slower the object will respond interactively."
msgstr "单个文本物体允许使用最多50000个字符；不过事先警告的是，单个文本物体使用的字符越多，物体的交互响应会变得更慢。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/texts/introduction.rst:43
msgid ""
"When you switch between *Object Mode* and *Edit Mode*, the *Font* panel remains the same. This means that its settings "
"can be applied equally in both modes, and this implies that you cannot apply them to just a part of the text. So font, "
"size, and so on, are common to all letters in a *Text* object. There is just one exception: the *Bold* or *Italic* "
"buttons control properties specific to each letter (this is a way to use up to four different fonts in a text)."
msgstr ""
"在 *物体模式* 和 *编辑模式* 之间切换时， *字体* 面板维持不变。这意味着可以在两种模式下同样地应用这些设置，也意味着这些"
"设置无法单独作用于文本的一部分。所以同一个 *文本* 物体中字符的字体、尺寸等是相同的。只有一个例外： *粗体* 或 *斜体* 按"
"钮控制的属性可以指定至单个字符(这是在同一文体中使用最多4种字体的方法)。"

